## 3. Dynamic Imports — Composants et analytics en différé

### Composants lourds (CRA — React.lazy)

```tsx
// Pages : toutes lazy-loadées (déjà dans kb-performance)
const Home = lazy(() => import('./pages/Home'))

// Composants lourds non critiques au premier rendu
const Chatbot     = lazy(() => import('./components/common/Chatbot'))
const MonacoEditor = lazy(() => import('./components/editors/MonacoEditor'))
const MapView     = lazy(() => import('./components/MapView'))
```

### Composants lourds (Next.js — next/dynamic)

```tsx
import dynamic from 'next/dynamic'

// Composant sans SSR (localStorage, browser APIs, WebGL)
const Chatbot = dynamic(
  () => import('@/components/common/Chatbot'),
  { ssr: false }
)

// Composant lourd avec SSR
const RichEditor = dynamic(
  () => import('@/components/RichEditor').then(m => m.RichEditor),
  { loading: () => <div className="animate-pulse h-40 bg-gray-100 rounded-xl" /> }
)
```

### Analytics et scripts tiers — différer après hydratation (Next.js)

```tsx
// layout.tsx
import dynamic from 'next/dynamic'

const Analytics    = dynamic(() => import('@vercel/analytics/react').then(m => ({ default: m.Analytics })), { ssr: false })
const CookieBanner = dynamic(() => import('@/components/CookieBanner'), { ssr: false })

export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <html>
      <body>
        {children}
        <Analytics />       {/* chargé après hydratation */}
        <CookieBanner />    {/* idem */}
      </body>
    </html>
  )
}
```

### Analytics et scripts tiers — différer après idle (CRA)

```tsx
// Déjà couvert par requestIdleCallback dans kb-performance
// Pattern identique pour tout script non critique
useEffect(() => {
  const load = () => import('@/lib/analytics').then(m => m.initAnalytics())
  if ('requestIdleCallback' in window) {
    window.requestIdleCallback(load, { timeout: 3000 })
  } else {
    window.addEventListener('load', load, { once: true })
  }
}, [])
```

